                " \n \nINTERNAL / EXTERNAL VACANCY\n \nIVANPLATS (Pty) Ltd, a subsidiary of Ivanhoe Mines, is advancing the development of its world-class palladium-rhodium-nickel-copper-gold project in the Limpopo Province near Mokopane. This unique mineral deposit will be exploited using large mechanised state-of-the-art underground mining methods, deploying the latest technology to develop this \u201cmine of the future\u201d. Suitably qualified and experienced candidates are invited to apply for the following vacancies required for the project development. \n \nMOBILIFT OPERATORS X 2 REF: IVP-FIN-12 \n \nSuitable candidates must possess the following minimum qualifications and skills: \n\u2022 Grade 12. \n\u2022 Certified competent as a Mobilift Operator and or Forklift driver. \n\u2022 Valid EB Driver\u2019s License. \n \nSuitable candidates must have the following work experience: \n\u2022 At least 1 years\u2019 experience as a forklift or mobilift driver within mining and construction environment. \n \nThe successful candidate will be responsible for, but not be limited to: \n\u2022 Daily inspection and completion of equipment checklist before the commencement of work \n\u2022 Load and unload bundles from trucks and move containers to storage bins. \n\u2022 Safety and Packing \n\u2022 Organising the storeroom \n\u2022 Loading and Unloading Delivery Vehicles \n\u2022 General adhoc tasks \n \n \nApplications must be forwarded to recruitments@ivanplats.com or www.ivanhoecommunities.com on or before the closing date. The company will NOT consider applications received after the closing date. \n \nClosing date: 05 November 2023 \n \nPreference will be given to Historically Disadvantaged South Africans (HDSA) from local communities surrounding Ivanplats Platreef mine. Applications are only open to South African Citizens Permanent RSA Residents that is fully vaccinated against COVID-19. \n \nShould you not hear from the Company within 14 days of the closing date, you should assume that your application has not been successful.\n \n \n \n ",
                " \n \n \n \nINTERNAL / EXTERNAL VACANCY \n \nIVANPLATS (Pty) Ltd, a subsidiary of Ivanhoe Mines, is advancing the development of its world-class palladium-rhodium-nickel-copper-gold project in the Limpopo Province near Mokopane. This unique mineral deposit will be exploited using large mechanised state-of-the-art underground mining methods, deploying the latest technology to develop this \u201cmine of the future\u201d. Suitably qualified and experienced candidates are invited to apply for the following vacancies required for the project development. \n \nSTOREMAN X 1 REF: IVP FIN- 11 \n \nSuitable candidates must possess the following minimum qualifications and skills: \n\u2022 Grade 12 \n\u2022 Drivers Licence \n\u2022 Basic math and recording abilities. \n\u2022 MS Office intermediate \n \nSuitable candidates must have the following work experience: \n\u2022 2 years related experience. \n\u2022 Excellent organizational skills \n \nThe successful candidate will be responsible for, but not be limited to: \n\u2022 Liaise with procurement staff to list expected deliveries. \n\u2022 Receive shipments and sign paperwork upon receipt. \n\u2022 Unload packages from incoming trucks. \n\u2022 Inspect contents to ensure they are undamaged. \n\u2022 Verify packages according to order and invoices (quantity, quality, price) \n\u2022 Contact supplier or shipper if a mistake is identified. \n\u2022 Assume responsibility for returning unsatisfactory shipments or receiving replacements. \n\u2022 Label deliveries and allocate them to their designated place. \n \n \nApplications must be forwarded to recruitments@ivanplats.com, www.ivanhoecommunities.com  on or before the closing date. The company will NOT consider applications received after the closing date. \n \nClosing date: 05 November 2023 \n \nPreference will be given to Historically Disadvantaged South Africans (HDSA) from local communities surrounding Ivanplats Platreef mine. Applications are only open to South African Citizens and Should you not hear from the Company within 14 days of the closing date, you should assume that your application has not been successful. Permanent RSA Residents that are fully vaccinated against COVID-19.\n \n \n \n ",
                " \n \n \n \nINTERNAL / EXTERNAL VACANCY \n \nIVANPLATS (Pty) Ltd, a subsidiary of Ivanhoe Mines, is advancing the development of its world-class palladium-rhodium-nickel-copper-gold project in the Limpopo Province near Mokopane. This unique mineral deposit will be exploited using large mechanised state-of-the-art underground mining methods, deploying the latest technology to develop this \u201cmine of the future\u201d. Suitably qualified and experienced candidates are invited to apply for the following vacancies required for the project development.\n \nBUYER ASSISTANT X 2 REF : IVP-FIN-09 \n \nSuitable candidates must possess the following minimum qualifications and skills: \n\u2022 Grade 12 \n\u2022 Degree or diploma in procurement or equivalent qualification in related field. \n\u2022 Proficiency in Microsoft Office. \n \nSuitable candidates must have the following work experience: \n\u2022 2 years relevant experience in procurement department. \n\u2022 Experience within the Mining industry will be advantageous. \n\u2022 Experience with Microsoft Office (Word, Excel, and PowerPoint). \n\u2022 Ability to multi-task and perform under pressure. \n \nThe successful candidate will be responsible for, but not be limited to: \n\u2022 identify and evaluate potential suppliers, establish, and maintain supplier relationships, and implement effective sourcing strategies. \n\u2022 ensuring accurate documentation and alignment with budgetary constraints. \n\u2022 Generate and process purchase orders for required goods and services. \n\u2022 Expedite, Monitor and track order status to ensure timely execution. \n\u2022 Manage and execute procurement processes at the project site, including raising purchase requisitions, obtaining quotes, and issuing purchase orders. \n\u2022 Maintain clear and effective communication with internal and external stakeholders. \n \n \nApplications must be forwarded to recruitments@ivanplats.com or www.ivanhoecommunities.com on or before the closing date. The company will NOT consider applications received after the closing date. \n \nClosing date: 05 November 2023 \n \nPreference will be given to Historically Disadvantaged South Africans (HDSA) from local communities surrounding Ivanplats Platreef mine. Applications are only open to South African Citizens and Permanent RSA Residents that are fully vaccinated against COVID-19. \n \nShould you not hear from the Company within 14 days of the closing date, you should assume that your application has not been successful.\n \n \n \n \n ",
                " \n \n \n \nINTERNAL / EXTERNAL VACANCY \n \nIVANPLATS (Pty) Ltd, a subsidiary of Ivanhoe Mines, is advancing the development of its world-class palladium-rhodium-nickel-copper-gold project in the Limpopo Province near Mokopane. This unique mineral deposit will be exploited using large mechanised state-of-the-art underground mining methods, deploying the latest technology to develop this \u201cmine of the future\u201d. Suitably qualified and experienced candidates are invited to apply for the following vacancies required for the project development. \n \nDRIVER X 1 REF: IVP FIN- 10 \n \nSuitable candidates must possess the following minimum qualifications and skills: \n\u2022 Grade 12 \n\u2022 Code 14 Drivers Licence with PDP \n\u2022 Defensive driving certificate would be advantageous. \n\u2022 Be honest and show integrity Sober habits Clear criminal record \n \nSuitable candidates must have the following work experience: \n\u2022 3 years driving and delivery experience. \n \nThe successful candidate will be responsible for, but not be limited to: \n\u2022 Drives vehicles following Company standard operating procedures and adhering to National Road Safety Codes to safe-guard passengers and goods being transported ensuring continued serviceability of the vehicle(s). \n\u2022 Checking parcels together with supervisor before loading into the vehicle always adhere to the New Dispatch Loading procedure. \n\u2022 Delivering the parcels to the customers on your designated route as per route schedule and trip sheet. \n\u2022 Conducts mandatory pre-start checks on the vehicles before using them and records any defects noticed. \n\u2022 Replenishes fluid levels and tyre pressure as and when needed. Brings to the attention of supervisor any major faults. \n\u2022 Cleans vehicle as and when necessary. \n\u2022 Undertakes national trips as instructed. \n\u2022 Prepares vehicle for trips outside of the mine property as required. Obtains relevant documentation for the vehicle. \n \n \nApplications must be forwarded to recruitments@ivanplats.com,  www.ivanhoecommunities.com on or before the closing date. The company will NOT consider applications received after the closing date. \n \nClosing date: 05 November 2023 \n \nPreference will be given to Historically Disadvantaged South Africans (HDSA) from local communities surrounding Ivanplats Platreef mine. Applications are only open to Permanent RSA Residents that is fully vaccinated against COVID-19. \n \nShould you not hear from the Company within 14 days of the closing date, you should assume that your application has not been successful.\n \n \n \n ",
                " \n \n \n \nINTERNAL / EXTERNAL VACANCY\n \nIVANPLATS (Pty) Ltd, a subsidiary of Ivanhoe Mines, is advancing the development of its world-class palladium-rhodium-nickel-copper-gold project in the Limpopo Province near Mokopane. This unique mineral deposit will be exploited using large mechanised state-of-the-art underground mining methods, deploying the latest technology to develop this \u201cmine of the future\u201d. Suitably qualified and experienced candidates are invited to apply for the following vacancies required for the project development. \n \nMECHANICAL FOREMAN X 1 (REF: IVP-PL-07) \n \nSuitable candidates must possess the following minimum qualifications and skills: \n\u2022 N4 Certificate in Mechanical Engineering- National Diploma in Mechanical Engineering is advantageous. \n\u2022 Qualified Mechanical Artisan with Trade Certificate in either: Boilermaking, Fitter and Turner or Millwright from recognized/accredited institution. \n\u2022 Valid code EB 8 driver\u2019s license. \n \nSuitable candidates must have the following work experience: \n\u2022 10 years' mining experience with 5 years artisan experience \n\u2022 Experience in Crushers, Mills, Larox Filter, Compressors, Pumps Flotation cells is advantageous. \n \nThe successful candidate will be responsible for, but not be limited to: \n\u2022 Coordinate tasks according to priorities and plans. \n\u2022 Allocate general and daily responsibilities. \n\u2022 Supervise the use of machinery and equipment. \n\u2022 Resolve problems when they arise. \n\u2022 Communicate with supervisors to inform on maintenance activities and availability of equipment. \n\u2022 Ensure the execution of scheduled and non-scheduled Mechanical repairs and installation work as required. \n\u2022 Co-ordinate maintenance as well as statutory inspections and audits by internal and external service providers. \n\u2022 Administrative duties to ensure record accuracy, spares availability within budget. \n\u2022 Supervise and inspect team members daily activities, offer coaching and on the job training to ensure maintenance according to organizational standards. \n \n \nApplications must be forwarded to recruitments@ivanplats.com or www.ivanhoecommunities.com on or before the closing date. The company will NOT consider applications received after the closing date\n.\nClosing date: 02 November 2023 \n \nPreference will be given to Historically Disadvantaged South Africans (HDSA) from local communities surrounding Ivanplats Platreef mine. Applications are only open to Permanent RSA Residents that is fully vaccinated against COVID-19. \n \nShould you not hear from the Company within 14 days of the closing date, you should assume that your application has not been successful.\n \n \n \n \n ",
                " \n \n \n \nINTERNAL / EXTERNAL VACANCY \n \nIVANPLATS (Pty) Ltd, a subsidiary of Ivanhoe Mines, is advancing the development of its world-class palladium-rhodium-nickel-copper-gold project in the Limpopo Province near Mokopane. This unique mineral deposit will be exploited using large mechanised state-of-the-art underground mining methods, deploying the latest technology to develop this \u201cmine of the future\u201d. Suitably qualified and experienced candidates are invited to apply for the following vacancies required for the project development. \n \nELECTRICAL FOREMAN X 1 (REF: IVP-PL-06) \n \nSuitable candidates must possess the following minimum qualifications and skills: \n\u2022 Matric \n\u2022 N4 Heavy current or National Diploma in Electrical Engineering is advantageous.\n\u2022 Qualified Electrical Trade Test Certificate at recognized/accredited institution. \n\u2022 Valid code EB 8 driver\u2019s license. \n \nSuitable candidates must have the following work experience: \n\u2022 10 years' mining experience with 4 years supervisory experience. \n\u2022 PGM Plant equipment experience. \n\u2022 MV experience. \n \nThe successful candidate will be responsible for, but not be limited to: \n\u2022 Ensure the execution of scheduled and non-scheduled electrical repairs and installation work as required. \n\u2022 Communicate with supervisors to inform on maintenance activities and availability of equipment. \n\u2022 Supervise and inspect team members daily activities, offer coaching and on the job training to ensure maintenance according to organizational standards \n\u2022 Co-ordinate maintenance as well as statutory inspections and audits by internal and external service providers \n\u2022 Provide on-site direction and leadership for workers to complete jobs within specific guidelines that include quality standards, time requirements, and budget considerations. \n\u2022 Organize and plan projects, directing work, inspection of installations for quality, making sure Mine code standards are met, whilst job safety remains a priority. \n \n \nApplications must be forwarded to recruitments@ivanplats.com or www.ivanhoecommunities.com on or before the closing date. The company will NOT consider applications received after the closing date. \n \nClosing date: 02 November 2023 \n \nPreference will be given to Historically Disadvantaged South Africans (HDSA) from local communities surrounding Ivanplats Platreef mine. Applications are only open to Permanent RSA Residents that is fully vaccinated against COVID-19. \n \nShould you not hear from the Company within 14 days of the closing date, you should assume that your application has not been successful.\n \n \n \n \n ",
                " \n \n \n \nINTERNAL / EXTERNAL VACANCY\n \nIVANPLATS (Pty) Ltd, a subsidiary of Ivanhoe Mines, is advancing the development of its world-class palladium-rhodium-nickel-copper-gold project in the Limpopo Province, near Mokopane. This unique mineral deposit will be exploited using large mechanized, state-of-the-art underground mining methods, deploying the latest technology to create this 'mine of the future.' We invite suitably qualified and experienced candidates to apply for the following vacancies required for the project's development. \n \nSECTIONAL VENTILATION ENGINEER X 1 (REF: IVP-VEN-02) \n \nApplicants must be in possession of the following: \n\u2022 Chamber of Mines (CoM) Certificate in Mine Environmental Control (MEC). \n\u2022 Membership in the Mine Ventilation Society. \n \nAdvantageous Qualifications: \n\u2022 Degree in Mining or Engineering. \n\u2022 Completion of specialized technical programs (e.g., Ventsim). \n\u2022 Registration with SAIOH as an Occupational Hygienist. \n \nWork Experience: \n\u2022 Minimum of 7 years of post-qualification experience in mine ventilation. \n \nResponsibilities Include: \n\u2022 Ensuring compliance with all legal requirements specified in the legal appointment and adherence to Ivanplats standards, procedures, and policies. \n\u2022 Achieving legal compliance in ventilation and occupational hygiene. \n\u2022 Designing, implementing, and managing effective ventilation and occupational hygiene strategies and systems. \n\u2022 Reporting on ventilation and occupational hygiene findings and trends. \n\u2022 Active participation in projects and effective project management. \n\u2022 Managing budgets and cost containment. \n\u2022 Efficient management of resources and assets, including asset management. \n\u2022 Overseeing risk assessment and auditing processes. \n\u2022 Planning for medium-term ventilation and occupational hygiene (at least 5 years). \n\u2022 Contributing to the achievement of objectives and targets within the ventilation and occupational hygiene department and the operational area. \n\u2022 Supporting team effectiveness. \n \n \nTo apply please send your applications to recruitments@ivanplats.com or visit www.ivanhoecommunities.comon or before the closing date. The company will NOT consider applications received after the closing date. We welcome applications from permanent RSA residents who are fully vaccinated against COVID-19. \n \nClosing Date: 31 October 2023 \n \nPreference will be given to Historically Disadvantaged South Africans (HDSA) from local communities surrounding Ivanplats Platreef mine. Applications are only open to South African Citizens and Permanent RSA Residents. \n \nIf you do not receive a response from the company within 14 days of the closing date, please assume that your application has not been successful.\n \n \n \n \n ",
                " \n \n \n \nINTERNAL / EXTERNAL VACANCY \n \nIVANPLATS (Pty) Ltd, a subsidiary of Ivanhoe Mines, is advancing the development of its world-class palladium-rhodium-nickel-copper-gold project in the Limpopo Province, near Mokopane. This unique mineral deposit will be exploited using large mechanized, state-of-the-art underground mining methods, deploying the latest technology to create this 'mine of the future.' We invite suitably qualified and experienced candidates to apply for the following vacancies required for the project's development. \n \nOCCUPATIONAL HYGIENIST X 1 (REF: IVP-VEN-03) \n \nApplicants must be in possession of at least one of the following: \n\u2022 BSc Honours in Physiology (Occupational Hygiene) and Chamber of Mines (CoM) Intermediate Certificate in Mine Environmental Control (MEC) \n\u2022 Registration with the South African Institute of Occupational Hygiene (SAIOH) at the Occupational Hygienist level and CoM Intermediate Certificate in MEC (Appointment on behalf of an appointed Section 12) \n\u2022 CoM Certificate in MEC (Appointed 12.1) \n \nAdvantageous:\n\u2022 Registration with SAIOH at the Occupational Hygienist level and CoM Certificate in MEC, along with membership with the Mine Ventilation Society of South Africa (MVSA) (Appointed 12.1) \n \nWork Experience: \n\u2022 A minimum of 5 years of post-qualification experience in the field of occupational hygiene/mine ventilation. \n\u2022 At least 2 years of experience in a processing environment. \n \nResponsibilities Include: \n\u2022 Identifying workplace conditions that may lead to illness or adverse health effects. \n\u2022 Assessing, evaluating, and monitoring occupational health risks due to identified hazards. \n\u2022 Recommending control measures to mitigate such risks. \n\u2022 Auditing compliance with standards. \n\u2022 Analysing trends in occupational exposure data and linking data to specific occupational groups. \n\u2022 Establishing Occupational Hygiene objectives and targets. \n\u2022 Providing education and training to employees on occupational health hazards and risks. \n\u2022 Conducting incident investigations. \n\u2022 Adhering to mandatory codes of practices. \n\u2022 Ensuring the availability of Occupational Hygiene programs. \n\u2022 Promoting best practices. \n\u2022 Reporting on Occupational Hygiene. \n\u2022 Integrating and linking medical surveillance data with occupational exposure data to inform the medical surveillance program. \n \n \nTo apply, please send your applications to recruitments@ivanplats.com or visit www.ivanhoecommunities.com before the closing date. Please note that applications received after the closing date will not be considered. We welcome applications from permanent RSA residents who are fully vaccinated against COVID-19. \n \nClosing date: 31 October 2023 \n \nPreference will be given to Historically Disadvantaged South Africans (HDSA) from local communities surrounding Ivanplats Platreef mine. Applications are only open to South African Citizens and Permanent RSA Residents. \n \nShould you not hear from the Company within 14 days of the closing date, you should assume that your application has not been successful.\n \n \n \n ",
                "INTERNAL / EXTERNAL VACANCY \n \nIVANPLATS (Pty) Ltd, a subsidiary of Ivanhoe Mines, is advancing the development of its world-class palladium-rhodium-nickel-copper-gold project in the Limpopo Province near Mokopane. This unique mineral deposit will be exploited using large mechanised state-of-the-art underground mining methods, deploying the latest technology to develop this \u201cmine of the future\u201d. Suitably qualified and experienced candidates are invited to apply for the following vacancies required for the project development. \n \nPLANT OPERATOR X 1 (REF: IVP-PL-05) \nSuitable candidates must possess the following minimum qualifications and skills: \n\u2022 Grade 12. \n\u2022 Minimum of 3 years job experience as a Plant Operator is essential. \n\u2022 Valid South African Driving License. \n \nSuitable candidates must have the following work experience: \n\u2022 Min 5 years\u2019 experience in a PGM production plant. \n\u2022 Proven plant operation experience in PGM plant crushing, grinding, flotation and filtration. \n\u2022 Valid medical certificate or be medically fit in order to obtain such a certificate. \n\u2022 Computer literate with Microsoft Excel, Word, Power Point, Outlook and Internet\n \nThe successful candidate will be responsible for, but not be limited to: \n\u2022 Owner team commissioning of the concentrator. \n\u2022 Do proper shift hand over on all required information to the next shift. \n\u2022 Meet operational targets for the shift. \n\u2022 Maintain a reliable reporting and communication system that is in place. \n\u2022 Ensure discipline is maintained in the work area (absenteeism, time management, overtime, misconduct (etc.) \n\u2022 Check staffing figures at start of shift and ensure that all plant activities are functionally covered. \n\u2022 Familiarise him/herself with production process activities, trends and brief operators accordingly at the start of each shift. \n\u2022 Take corrective actions accordingly and eliminate deviations in the processing plant which may influence production or safety. \n\u2022 Ensure work schedules are adhered to by all team members. \n\u2022 Adhere apply SHE and OHS principles. \n\u2022 Ensure compliance with all HR policies, procedures and standards. \n\u2022 Audit of sampling equipment and ensure adherence to procedure. \n\u2022 Apply the Ivanplats principles in all team interactions and take personal responsibility for your safety and others to ensure zero harm and elimination of fatalities and loss time Injuries in accordance with the Ivanplats Standards, and Mine Health and Safety Act. \n \n \nApplications must be forwarded to recruitments@ivanplats.com or www.ivanhoecommunities.com on or before the closing date. The company will NOT consider applications received after the closing date. \n \nClosing date: 30 October 2023 \n \nPreference will be given to Historically Disadvantaged South Africans (HDSA) from local communities surrounding Ivanplats Platreef mine. Applications are only open to Permanent RSA Residents that is fully vaccinated against COVID-19. \n \nShould you not hear from the Company within 14 days of the closing date, you should assume that your application has not been successful.",
                "INTERNAL / EXTERNAL VACANCY\n \nIVANPLATS (Pty) Ltd, a subsidiary of Ivanhoe Mines, is advancing the development of its world-class palladium-rhodium-nickel-copper-gold project in the Limpopo Province near Mokopane. This unique mineral deposit will be exploited using large mechanised state-of-the-art underground mining methods, deploying the latest technology to develop this \u201cmine of the future\u201d. Suitably qualified and experienced candidates are invited to apply for the following vacancies required for the project development. \n \nPLANT FOREMAN X 1 (REF: IVP-PL-04) \n \nSuitable candidates must be in possession of the following minimum qualifications and skills: \n\u2022 Grade 12 /NQF Level 4 is essential. \n\u2022 Minimum of 8 years job experience as a Plant Shift Leader/Senior Control Room Operator is essential. \n\u2022 Valid South African Driving License. \n \nSuitable candidates must have the following work experience: \n\u2022 Min 10 years\u2019 experience in a PGM production plant. \n\u2022 Proven plant operation experience in PGM plant crushing, grinding, flotation and filtration. \n\u2022 Valid medical certificate or be medically fit in order to obtain such a certificate. \n\u2022 Computer literate with Microsoft Excel, Word, Power Point, Outlook and Internet\n \nThe successful candidate will be responsible for, but not be limited to: \n\u2022 Owner team commissioning of the concentrator \n\u2022 Check staffing figures at start of shift and ensure that all plant activities are functionally covered. \n\u2022 Familiarise him/herself with production process activities, trends and brief operators accordingly at the start of each shift. \n\u2022 Take corrective actions and instruct staff accordingly in significant deviations in the processing plant which may influence production or safety. \n\u2022 Ensure work schedules are adhered to by all team members. \n\u2022 Adhere apply SHE and OHS principles. \n\u2022 Ensure compliance with all HR policies, procedures and standards. \n\u2022 Audit of sampling equipment and ensure adherence to procedure. \n\u2022 Apply the Ivanplats principles in all team interactions and take personal responsibility for your safety and others to ensure zero harm and elimination of fatalities and loss time Injuries in accordance with the Ivanplats Standards, and Mine Health and Safety Act. \n \n \nApplications must be forwarded to recruitments@ivanplats.com or www.ivanhoecommunities.com on or before the closing date. The company will NOT consider applications received after the closing date. \n \nClosing date: 30 October 2023 \n \nPreference will be given to Historically Disadvantaged South Africans (HDSA) from local communities surrounding Ivanplats Platreef mine. Applications are only open to Permanent RSA Residents that are fully vaccinated against COVID-19. \n \nShould you not hear from the Company within 14 days of the closing date, you should assume that your application has not been successful."
