                " \n \nMECHANIC GENERAL GLOBAL GRADE 08\nBellville, ZA\nFull-Time\nEquipment\nMechanic General Global Grade 08\nApply To Position\nApply Using LinkedIn\n \nKey Outputs\nCarry out scheduled services, maintenance, and repairs (Disassemble, inspect and assemble) on Earthmoving Equipment on customer sites or at Barloworld Equipment sites.\nCarry out Machine Inspections and Technical Analysis (TA\u2019s) on machines or components, compile accurate reports with recommendations to the customers.\nEfficiently trouble shoot and diagnose machine systems and carry out repairs to ensure optimal utilization and availability of machines.\nMaintain professional image when representing Barloworld Equipment\nMaintain and work according to BWE Contamination Standards\nEnsure that the ultimate quality standards are maintained on the work performed according to OEM standards.\nControl own admin (labour booking, service reports, part returns, expenses etc.)\nFollow through to ensure that quality and productivity standards of own work are consistently and accurately maintained\nEnsure safe work practice\n \nQualification, Experience and Competencies\nMatric/ Grade 12\nQualified in relevant trade, red seal (e.g. Earthmoving Equipment Mechanic/ Diesel Mechanic)\nMinimum of five (5) years post qualification experience on Caterpillar machines.\nMachine specific technical knowledge and skills on Caterpillar Equipment systems.\nGood understanding of operation systems on Caterpillar equipment.\nMust be able to read and understand Caterpillar equipment system schematics.\nSound interpersonal and communication skills\nGood technical report writing\nBasic business and financial understanding\nComputer Literacy (SIS, STW and ET) knowledge\nGood trouble shooting and problem-solving skills\nApplicable product knowledge\nDrivers licence \u2013 Code B\nUnderstanding of supplier warranty systems, policies and procedures\nKnowledge of ISO Quality systems\nKnowledge and implementation of Contamination Control principles\nUnderstanding of supplier warranty systems, policies and procedures\nKnowledge of ISO Quality systems\nKnowledge and implementation of Contamination Control principles\n \n \n \n \n ",
