                " \n \n \n \nSERVICE SUPERVISOR (DRILLS) GLOBAL GRADE 10\nImpunzi, ZA\nFull-Time\nService Supervisor (Drills) Global Grade 10\nApply To Position\nApply Using LinkedIn\n \nKey Output\n\u2022 The MARC supervisor is responsible for all the labour supervision on site.\n\u2022 He ensures all work carried out is safe and conforms to the prevailing labour or mining laws.\n\u2022 The supervisor will ensure the workplace is safe and conforms to regulations.\n\u2022 He will make sure all the labour work requirements are controlled and necessary licences and certificates are obtained and kept up to date.\n\u2022 He ensures that the Barloworld work standards are observed; all parts authorizations and service reports are signed.\n\u2022 He co-ordinates and executes the plan drawn up by the site planner.\n\u2022 The supervisor executes the plan as efficiently as possible giving feedback on any deviations.\n\u2022 He will confirm that all work done have risk assessments completed before proceeding.\n\u2022 After PM inspections will be done by the supervisor to ensure the quality of work.\n\u2022 The supervisor is to ensure that all facilities or work aids are arranged for work in the plan and if necessary, co-ordinate these with the customer or Barloworld.\n\u2022 Achievement of financial targets and effective control of Workshop expenses\n\u2022 Ensure correct allocation of all machine warranty incidents.\n\u2022 Achievement of site KPI\u2019s.\n\u2022 Effective self-management and performance ownership.\n\u2022 Entrench an Employment Value Creation culture in the Workshop.\n\u2022 Achievement of cost centre financial targets and Key Performance Indicators\n\u2022 Resolve internal customer queries.\n\u2022 Ensure effective communication between team and management.\n\u2022 Ensure service work is carried out in compliance with quality standards (OEM Guidelines)\n\u2022 Apply Barloworld Equipment leadership philosophy.\n\u2022 Achievement of a team environment that enables maximum productivity and profitability (Performance management of team)\n\u2022 Competency development of team \u2013 one our training\n\u2022 Take ownership and manage all 2.9.2 appointment responsibilities.,\n \nExperience and Competencies Qualification\n\u2022 Grade12\n\u2022 Minimum of 6 years\u2019 experience as Mechanic General, Trade Test qualified in relevant trade (e.g. Diesel Mechanic/ Earthmoving Equipment Mechanic) post apprenticeship or learn ship experience.\n\u2022 Experienced trouble shooting and problem-solving skills on Earthmoving Equipment Machines.\n\u2022 Well imbedded machine specific technical knowledge and skills.\n\u2022 Sound interpersonal and communication Good technical report writing skills.\n\u2022 Basic business and financial understanding and Computer literate\n\u2022 Good business writing and experiences on Caterpillar machine and product knowledge.\n \n \n \n ",
